sentences: He released his debut album Smash with Warp Records in 2005.
After his acid house debut on Pumpking records in 1996, Sound of Barclay records released the "Sense Juice" and "Gourmet" EPs under the name Jackson & His Computer Band.
In 2003 his fourth single, album opener "Utopia", was released.
"Utopia", from the album Smash, was used in the O2 ‘bubble’ ad campaign.
"Pump", "More" and "Seal," tracks from the Glow album, were featured in Adult Swim bumps that aired during the summer of 2016.

He performed at European summer festivals in Nîmes (France), Zurich (Switzerland) and Dour Festival (Belgium).
His second album Glow was released on Warp Records on 2 September 2013.
